lor": "f7e101", "default": false, "description": "Area: Trait system"}, {"id": 650731663, "node_id": "MDU6TGFiZWw2NTA3MzE2NjM=", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/labels/C-bug", "name": "C-bug", "color": "f5f1fd", "default": false, "description": "Category: This is a bug."}, {"id": 2311820664, "node_id": "MDU6TGFiZWwyMzExODIwNjY0", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/labels/A-cross-crate-reexports", "name": "A-cross-crate-reexports", "color": "f7e101", "default": false, "description": "Area: Documentation that has been re-exported from a different crate"}], "state": "open", "locked": false, "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "milestone": null, "comments": 2, "created_at": "2021-09-22T19:23:43Z", "updated_at": "2021-09-30T20:48:38Z", "closed_at": null, "author_association": "MEMBER", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "There is a \"bug\" related to cross-crate re-exports and `where` clauses: In the `core` docs, the impl looks like this (which is how it's actually written in the source):\r\n\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/37223377/134408031-f9f54201-6faa-43fc-97f7-d46444c47c7c.png)\r\n\r\nBut in the `std` docs, the impl looks like this, with all of the bounds expressed as `where` clauses:\r\n\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/37223377/134408070-e6cb807b-459c-490e-92c6-2a9ac6d4ffa0.png)\r\n\r\nI think the re-exported version is actually better, because it's easier to read, but they should at least be consistent.\r\n\r\n_Originally posted by @camelid in https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/issues/88809#issuecomment-925245936_\r\n\r\n**Note:** It's possible this is triggered by any re-exports, not just cross-crate ones, but I haven't checked.", "closed_by": null, "reactions": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/89180/reactions", "total_count": 0, "+1": 0, "-1": 0, "laugh": 0, "hooray": 0, "confused": 0, "heart": 0, "rocket": 0, "eyes": 0}, "timeline_url": "https://api.githu